CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, December 27, 1937, p. unknown, reads: "Time out with an inquiring camera. At  Sewickly [Sewickley], Pa., Fred Gould (left) was caught swapping good chatter with George Greenlee, brother of the well known Gus Greenlee, and Squire Milton (right).  It was a good point for getting together as the friendly little rally was at the Sunset Gardens (cabaret)."
TitMainTitle: Fred Gould, George Greenlee, and Squire Milton posed in Sunset Gardens Cabaret Club, with waitress in background, Sewickley
